<br>
Step 1) Change all lure spells to unresistable (no resistance check at all) the mana/damage ration makes this balanced.<br>
<br>
Step 2) Take the previous formulas used with the Lure saves, and apply them to a new line of spells called the innvocation line.<br>
<br>
Invocation of Frost:<br>
mana: 600<br>
Time: 8s<br>
Save: As previous lure of frost save<br>
DD: 500dmg +50dmg/lvl<br>
Dot: 5% of the target's HP over 10 ticks<br>
Spell Level: 52<br>
<br>
Invocation of Fire:<br>
mana: 600<br>
Time: 8s<br>
Save: As previous lure of flame save<br>
DD: 700dmg +50dmg/lvl<br>
Dot: 7% of the target's HP over 10 ticks<br>
Spell Level: 55<br>
<br>
Invocation of Lightning:<br>
mana: 600<br>
Time: 8s<br>
Save: As previous lure of lightning save<br>
DD: 800dmg +50dmg/lvl<br>
Dot: 9% of the target's HP over 10 ticks<br>
Spell Level: 58<br>
<br>
Invocation of Ice:<br>
mana: 600<br>
Time: 8s<br>
Save: As previous lure of ice save<br>
DD: 900dmg +50dmg/lvl<br>
Dot: 11% of the target's HP over 10 ticks<br>
Spell Level: 59<br>
<br>
Invocation of Sorcerer:<br>
mana: 1200<br>
Time: 8s<br>
Save: 3 saves at -50 (ice/fire/Magic) must pass all 3 to resist<br>
DD: 1100dmg <br>
Dot: 15% of the target's HP over 10 ticks<br>
Effect: Concusion (Caster removed from hatelist)<br>
Component: 3 Batwings, 1 undead froglok tounge, 1 basilisk tounge, 1 werebat wing, 1 spiderling eye<br>
Spell Level: 60<br>
<br>
3) Sunstrike increased to 2400 damage, ice and lightning based DD of 2400 damage added in at lvl 60<br>
<br>
<br>
That my friends, is how to balance wizards in the post 50 game. In the 49 and lower game, increase our inate mana regen (2 to 3 times) and begin reducing resists at lvl 35 by -10, give it a -1 to fire/cold/magic saves on our dd per level (ie lvl 60's would have an inate -35 on all their spells (With the exception of invocation/lures))<br>
<br>
Comments please<br>
<br>
Silvius Wayfarer <br>
35th wizard of Drinal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uborim69.showPublicProfile?language=EN>borim 69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/11/01 11:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> reply</span><hr size=1>  We dont need no stinking dots hehe not flaming you but I dont want dots I dont want rains.I want  pillars and DD never had much luck with rains seems like it always breaks the root,aggros the mobs something undesirable anyway. More damage less mana cost per spell is what i say. Although I do like the way you have the DD arranged x amount of hp per lvl.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umyght.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Myght</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/12/01 6:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ugh, Keep your Wrath line and give us this...</span><hr size=1> dot is not our thing. and thats a lot of annoying reagents hehe.<br>
<br>
plus, u dont know how bad the resists are with lures. plane of sky 7th isle. i tried out lure of lightning, flame, frost and they were all resisted 100% on all 3 types of drakes. thats with tash, not sure on malo.<br>
<br>
plane of growth, i casted roughly 15 lures (mod rods) on Fayl Everstrong. i landed 2. with tash, malo. so i did 1200ish dmg on a 200k hp mob using 4500ish mana. <br>
<br>
<br>
id be happy if they gave us totally unresistable nukes that isnt mob specific and uses no reagents. 2 peridots is a joke. and we'e useless till lvl 60? wtf do we do on mobs other than dragons and giants?<br>
<br>
we also need all our previous nukes upgraded (PB, Rains, single target DD). our pillar line is pretty good tho. the rest are way too close or worse than mages. on some spell levels, druids get better nukes. we dont get to heal, summon a pet, feed mana, buff, etc.. only thing we can do is nuke. so our nuking abilities should be clearly better than ALL other classes.<br>
<br>
even changing all that wouldnt 'balance' us since were so much useless than melees but id be happy enough with the above changes.<br>
<br>
i know verant said theyre still working on balancing our class, but i havent seen ANYTHING impressive from them yet. just my little opinion.<br>
<br>
